  "text": "pton, UK) and cultured in Lurial-Bertani broth. The protein was expressed and the cells were lysed as described previously [CITATION_1] . Clarified lysates were bound to Fast-flow glutathione resin (GE Life Sciences). The bound resin was washed and treated overnight at 4°C with PreScission protease (20 U/ml resin; GE Life Sciences). The cleaved, eluted eIF2B␣ (now in the supernatant) was further purified [CITATION_2] .",
